Only if you have the fully unreasonable belief that the market acts instantaneously (which as a feedback mechanism it certainly does NOT), AND if you say that the market exists unmolested by various kinds of interference... can you dismiss the invisible hand.

The hand works better/faster when unmolested, and should be expected to act AFTER a change has happened.  What RETURNS equilibrium is the hand at work.

